`axios.get` returns a promise. The promise can be chained and awaited.
Your `helper` function returns `undefined`. You should return the result of the `axios.get`

```js
function helper(chiaUrl,videoThumbnails,index) {
     return axios.get(chiaUrl)
        .then((response) =&gt; {
            if (response.status == 200) {
                const $ = cheerio.load(response.data);
                const videoLink = $(&quot;div[id=load_anime] div iframe&quot;);
                videoThumbnails[index].thumbnailLink = videoLink.attr(&quot;src&quot;);    
            }
        })
        .finally(()=&gt; {

        })
}
```

It&#39;s also worth noting that if you return something within the `.then`, it will be the result of the await (so that you don&#39;t have to pass in `videoThumbnails` and mutate it to get the result).

